quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  40,41,"O my people! How is it that I invite you to salvation, while you invite me to the Fire"
  40,42,"You invite me to disbelieve in Allah and associate with Him what I have no knowledge of, while I invite you to the Almighty, Most Forgiving"
  40,43,"There is no doubt that whatever ňĻidolsňļ you invite me to ňĻworshipňļ are not worthy to be invoked either in this world or the Hereafter.¬†ňĻUndoubtedly,ňļ our return is to Allah, and the transgressors will be the inmates of the Fire"
  40,44,"You will remember what I say to you, and I entrust my affairs to Allah. Surely Allah is All-Seeing of all ňĻHisňļ servants.‚ÄĚ"
  40,45,So Allah protected him from the evil of their schemes. And Pharaoh‚Äôs people were overwhelmed by an evil punishment
  40,46,"they are exposed to the Fire ňĻin their gravesňļ morning and evening. And on the Day the Hour will be established ňĻit will be saidňļ, ‚ÄúAdmit Pharaoh‚Äôs people into the harshest punishment ňĻof Hellňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  40,47,"ňĻConsider the Dayňļ when they will dispute in the Fire, and the lowly ňĻfollowersňļ will appeal to the arrogant ňĻleadersňļ, ‚ÄúWe were your ňĻdedicatedňļ followers, will you then shield us from a portion of the Fire?‚ÄĚ"
  40,48,"The arrogant will say, ‚ÄúWe are all in it! ňĻForňļ Allah has already passed judgment over ňĻHisňļ servants.‚ÄĚ"
  40,49,"And those in the Fire will cry out to the keepers of Hell,¬†‚ÄúPray to your Lord to lighten the torment for us ňĻevenňļ for one day!‚ÄĚ"
  40,50,"The keepers will reply, ‚ÄúDid your messengers not ňĻconstantlyňļ come to you with clear proofs?‚ÄĚ They will say, ‚ÄúYes ňĻthey didňļ.‚ÄĚ The keepers will say, ‚ÄúThen pray! Though the prayer of the disbelievers is only in vain.‚ÄĚ"
  40,51,"We certainly help Our messengers and the believers, ňĻbothňļ in this worldly life and on the Day the witnesses will stand forth ňĻfor testimonyňļ‚ÄĒ"
  40,52,"the Day the wrongdoers‚Äô excuses will be of no benefit to them. They will be condemned, and will have the worst outcome"
  40,53,"And indeed, We gave Moses ňĻtrueňļ guidance, and made the Children of Israel inherit the Scripture‚ÄĒ"
  40,54,a guide and a reminder to people of reason
  40,55,"So be patient ňĻO Prophetňļ, ňĻforňļ Allah‚Äôs promise is certainly true. Seek forgiveness for your shortcomings.¬†And glorify the praises of your Lord morning and evening"
  40,56,"Surely those who dispute Allah‚Äôs signs‚ÄĒwith no proof given to them‚ÄĒhave nothing in their hearts but greed for dominance, which they will never attain. So seek refuge in Allah. Indeed, He alone is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  40,57,"The creation of the heavens and the earth is certainly greater than the re-creation of humankind, but most people do not know"
  40,58,"Those blind ňĻto the truthňļ and those who can see are not equal, nor are those who believe and do good ňĻequalňļ to those who do evil. Yet you are hardly mindful"
  40,59,"The Hour is certainly coming, there is no doubt about it. But most people do not believe"
  40,60,"Your Lord has proclaimed, ‚ÄúCall upon Me, I will respond to you. Surely those who are too proud to worship Me will enter Hell, fully humbled.‚ÄĚ"
  40,61,"It is Allah Who has made the night for you to rest in and the day bright. Surely Allah is ever Bountiful to humanity, but most people are ungrateful"
  40,62,"That is Allah, your Lord, the Creator of all things. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. How can you then be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  40,63,This is how those who used to reject Allah‚Äôs signs were ňĻalsoňļ deluded
  40,64,"It is Allah Who made the earth a place of settlement for you and the sky a canopy. He shaped you ňĻin the wombňļ, perfecting your form. And He has provided you with what is good and lawful. That is Allah‚ÄĒyour Lord. So Blessed is Allah, Lord of all worlds"
  40,65,"He is the Ever-Living. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. So call upon Him with sincere devotion, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúAll praise is for Allah‚ÄĒLord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"